Parliament, Monday, 11 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Energy will be briefed by the Auditor-General of South Africa on the Department of Energy and its entities’ audit outcomes for the period 2017/18. Details of the meeting:
	Date: Tuesday, 12 February 2019
	Time: 11:00 – 13:00
	Venue: Committee Room 1, Upper Ground Floor, 90 Plein Street ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ENERGY, MR FIKILE MAJOLA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Yoliswa LanduParliamentary Communication ServicesTel: 021 403 8203Cell: 081 497 4694E-mail: ylandu@parliament.gov.za The Bill of Rights guarantees freedom of expression, as long as this freedom is not used as propaganda for war, incitement to violence or the advocacy of hatred based on race, ethnicity, gender or religion.Read more